  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Even it Up Campaign in Vietnam.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Based on the context analysis, Oxfam#s vision towards 2020 and the linkage with Oxfam#s Global Even it Up Campaign, inequality has been identified as the focused issue for Oxfam#s campaign in Vietnam for the period 2016-2019.

The four-year campaign will focus onpromoting public debates on the need to combat extreme inequalities, raising public awareness of the issue, enhancing the roles of CSOs in addressing inequalities and contributing to discussions and the progressive changes policies that address inequalities. The long-term goal of the campaign is that by 2019 there will be improvement on policy development/execution (or legislative change/policy change) to fight inequality and more effective re-distributive measures to address poverty and gender injustice. This will be backed up by solid evidences that extreme inequality is wrong, and stands in the way of people claiming their rights.

In the 1st year,we are seeking to make progress on 3 areas:
- Shifting the debates among the policy makers, media and citizen to make greater change possible from now until 2019. The debate will possibly include the increasing gap between the rich and the poor, state budget mobilisation through the fair fiscal system, and allocation to the lower tier public services (health care), socialisation and decentralisation policies in public service investment, out-of pocket payment from service users.
- Influence the agenda and focus of the existing Equality Coalition#s strategy, and enhance their roles in addressing inequality in health sector.
- Policy progress about the inequality in accessing quality social services (health) through more transparent and accountable information sharing mechanisms about state budget mobilisation and allocation to social services

In the 2nd year (2017), the objective of EiU campaign has been identified as &quot;#Enhancing the awareness of community on the origin of inequalities, which helps them to believe that inequalities is raised not only by nature or positive process but also by either negative process or subjective elements of political economy institution&quot;. Specifically, the objectives are:
- To increase a number of people involving in the campaign. Especially those willingly to joinin debates and to have their voices say against inequality.
- To inspire the youth to bring forward their points of view and to take action in order to change.
- To ameliorate the citizens# preconception that inequality is evident and unable to modify.</narrative>
  </description>
